  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>★ 4.6 / 37 Google reviews</span><span>Licensed · Insured</span><span>Same-day · 5 SoCal counties</span><span>$120 commercial diagnostic · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Montague Company — Ali Group, California manufacturer since 1857</h2>
    <p>Montague Company has manufactured commercial cooking equipment from Hayward, California since 1857 — 168 years of continuous California-based production. In July 2022, Ali Group completed its acquisition of Welbilt Inc., which included Montague; the brand is now part of Ali Group NA alongside Pitco and Frymaster (cluster 06 fryers), Champion and CMA (cluster 05 dishwashers), Manitowoc (cluster 03 ice), Beverage-Air (cluster 02 refrigeration), Kolpak/Master-Bilt/Nor-Lake (cluster 01 walk-in), and the broader post-2022 Ali Group family.</p>
    <p>For LA operators, the Hayward California manufacturing location delivers modest logistical advantages on some Montague-specific parts — California-sourced components reach LA in days rather than week-plus lead times. Most routine service parts still route through Ali Group's Winston-Salem NC distribution infrastructure, but California-manufactured specialty components (specific Grizzly charbroiler radiants, Vectaire custom controls, UFM broiler elements) sometimes ship direct from Hayward with shorter LA delivery times.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Montague commercial cooking equipment we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Grizzly — charbroiler-oven combination</h3><p>Montague's signature LA steakhouse product. Heavy-duty charbroiler on top (900–1,100°F radiant surface) with oven compartment integrated below. The combination delivers steakhouse charbroil plus side-dish roasting in one equipment footprint. Service: charbroiler radiants, oven thermostat, gas valve, door hinge.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Vectaire — convection flagship</h3><p>Montague's standalone full-size convection oven line. Gas or electric configurations. Common at LA casual-dining and mid-to-upper restaurant operations. Service pattern mirrors other commercial convection ovens: fan motor, thermostat, door hinge, heating element (electric) or burner ignitor (gas).</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>4-Series — range-ovens</h3><p>Traditional range-oven combination — burners on top, oven compartment below. Mid-volume LA restaurant back-of-house standard. Service spans range and oven diagnostic domains.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>UFM — underfired broilers</h3><p>Underfired broiler for high-radiant-intensity cooking. Specialty for steakhouse and specific restaurant-concept operations. Service: broiler element, radiant assembly, gas valve.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>LA steakhouse cluster — where the Grizzly lives</h2>
    <p>LA's steakhouse market runs substantial Montague Grizzly installations because the charbroiler-oven combination delivers what steakhouse kitchens need: extremely high charbroil temperatures for steak searing plus integrated oven capacity for sides, appetizers, and roasted accompaniments without separate equipment. Specific LA operations in our Montague service experience include Mastro's Steakhouse locations across Beverly Hills and Ocean Club in Newport Beach, STK restaurant group kitchens, high-end steakhouse concepts at hotel properties, and multiple independent operations in the upper steakhouse tier.</p>
    <p>Beyond steakhouses, LA casual-dining operations run Vectaire convection and 4-Series range-ovens where Montague's California manufacturing heritage plus Ali Group family parts availability delivers a sensible value proposition. Our service coverage spans all four major Montague product lines; Grizzly and Vectaire account for the bulk of LA service volume.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What Montague oven repair costs in LA</h2>
    <p>$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</p>
    <table class="price-table"><thead><tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical range (parts + labor)</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody><tr><td>Oven-compartment door gasket</td><td>$200–$340</td></tr><tr><td>Thermostat replacement</td><td>$200–$340</td></tr><tr><td>Door hinge service</td><td>$240–$420</td></tr><tr><td>Burner ignitor assembly</td><td>$240–$400</td></tr><tr><td>Gas valve replacement</td><td>$300–$500</td></tr><tr><td>Grizzly charbroiler radiant replacement</td><td>$320–$560</td></tr><tr><td>Vectaire convection fan motor</td><td>$320–$520</td></tr><tr><td>UFM broiler element</td><td>$340–$560</td></tr><tr><td>Control board replacement</td><td>$650–$1,100</td></tr><tr><td>Full Grizzly refurbish</td><td>$700–$1,200</td></tr></tbody></table>
    <p class="small">Most Montague calls land $350–$750 parts-and-labor. Grizzly charbroiler service runs at the higher end. See our <a href="/price-list/commercial-oven-repair-cost/">commercial oven repair cost guide</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

